text_occasion_en(259,'&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;Paris 1959. Manifesto, lectured at&nbsp;the Galerie Quatre Saisons on occasion of Alain Jouffroy&#039;s&nbsp;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt; mso-ansi-language: FR&quot;&gt;Anti-Proces&quot;. The o&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;riginal text is lost and was recontructed for the&nbsp;Paris exhibition catalogue&nbsp;of 1975. Published&nbsp;i.a. in: Catalogue of the world travelling&nbsp;museum exhibition,&nbsp;Paris,&nbsp;1975, exhibition catalogue, Cologne&nbsp;1980. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;font face=&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;letter-spacing: 0.3pt&quot;&gt;Hundertwasser spoke the text in French, repeating each sentence. Three&nbsp;bags of nettles were piled up on stage and cooked in a big copper. Hundred plastic spoons and paper plates were handed out to the audience. Hundertwasser and an assistant went throuth the audience and with a laddle they gave everyone a nettle into their plate, which hang from the plate on the left and on the right. Then he returned to the stage. As no one from the aucience wanted to try, he himself ate three nettles. As in the copper&nbsp;residues of detergents&nbsp;had remained, the nettle spinach tasted like soap and Hundertwasser felt queasy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;').

